                                "id": "01GR6AFCC93PF6T4EYVTXXYJY9",
                                "reference": "INSPIRATION",
                                "subject": "Inspiration"
                            },
                            "text": "Born in Atlanta, Texas, on January 26, 1892, Bessie Coleman was the first Black woman in the world to fly a plane. She was also the first African-American woman and the first Native American to hold a pilot's license. She was a high-profile figure in the media of the time and performed stunt maneuvers in numerous airshows."
                        },
